comments: Replay review of the foul called on Mitchell (SAC) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Mitchell initiates contact to Booker's (PHX) wrist that affects his jump shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Fox's (SAC) path and absorbs the contact.
Huerter (SAC) legally contests Bridges's (PHX) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Sabonis (SAC) establishes himself in a screening position in Bridges' (PHX) path and marginal arm contact occurs as he goes around the screen.
Ayton (PHX) legally contests Monk's (SAC) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Fox (SAC) taps the rebound away and incidental contact occurs with Craig (PHX).
Booker (PHX) initiates contact to Monk's (SAC) arms before making contact with the ball, affecting his shot attempt at the basket.
Huerter (SAC) cleanly steals the ball away from Bridges (PHX).
Booker (PHX) drives towards the basket and marginal body contact occurs as he comes together with Fox (SAC).
Huerter (SAC) places an arm against Craig's (PHX) back during the rebound but does not dislodge him from his position.
Huerter (SAC) commits a take foul on Booker (PHX).
Craig's (PHX) arm is not in a vertical position when he contests Barnes' (SAC) driving shot attempt, but the contact is marginal.
